        <p class="metadata">Posted by Mon Zafra (monzee) on 2009-12-08T04:46:19.000+0000</p> 
        <div class="body">
            <p>It seems to me that the captcha element is not designed to be validated against the regular validators since its captcha's validator expects the value to be an array with a specific format. IMHO though, there's no need to validate a captcha against anything other than its own validator. An input shorter than the expected length would also be caught by the captcha's validator.</p>

